definition.value: A nerolidol in which the double bond at position 6 adopts a cis-configuration.
An  acetylspermine carrying an acetyl group at position N(1).
A sesquiterpene that is (9aS)-5,6,7,8,9,9a-hexahydro-1H-benzo[7]annulene substituted by methyl groups at positions 3, 5, 5 and 9R. It is a pheromone produced by males of several Phyllotreta species.

A sesquiterpenoid that is bisabolane having double bonds at positions 2 and 9 as well as a hydroxy substituent at position 1 (the 1S,6S,7R-stereoisomer). It is a male produced sex pheromone of Tibraca limbativentris.

A C22 hydroxy fatty acid with the hydroxy group at the 13-position and intermediate in the synthesis of sophorosyloxydocosanoate; a yeast glycolipid with potential medical and chemical engineering applications.
An amino sugar whose structure comprises D-glucose having an amino substituent at position 2.
